Five people were killed by an on
coming train while crossing the tracks in the Nizhny Novgorod
region of  Russia â€™s Volga federal district,  RIA Novosti  reported.  A group of passengers had just left a commuter train when
struck by a second train, the Moscow-based news service said.
Three women and two men were killed, while a sixth man was
treated in a nearby hospital and released, the report said.  Local transportation officials have begun a preliminary
